The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Krishnagar, Aug. 11: A youth today committed suicide in a hospital toilet after being beaten up by villagers for stealing a cow.    
	Police said Amar Haldar of Dhubulia hanged himself in a toilet in Shaktinagar district hospital two hours after he was admitted. He was allegedly thrashed by villagers who caught him escaping with the cow.        
	Tamluk: About a hundred Bhoomi Uchchhed Pratirodh Committee activists sat on a dharna in front of Nandigram police station on Monday demanding restoration of peace. They squatted for an hour till police told them that raids would be launched to seize hidden arms.                                                                                                                                                                   
